{
    "content": "When he completes his vow by death, his eyes must be closed, his hands stretched out, his mouth shut, his legs extended, his jaws pulled, and his shrouds prepared. The shroud is required to consist of three pieces; an apron, a shirt, and a loincloth. However, it is recommended to add a fourth piece, which is a special wrap usually used by the people of Yemen, or any other loincloth. It is furthermore recommended to use a fifth piece of clothes with which the thighs and the hip are tied up. Moreover, it is recommended to used a sixth piece of clothes as a turban.\r\n\r\nIn addition, some camphor that has not been coped with fire may be added in a quantity ranging between thirteen and a third dirham, four mitigals, or one dirham at least. If this is unfeasible, any quantity may be used.\r\n\r\nOn each of these shrouds, the following words my be written down: so and so\r\n\r\n--يَشْهَدُ اَنْ لَاۤ اِلٰهَ اِلَّا اللهُ وَحْدَهُ لَا شَرِيْكَ لَهُ وَ اَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا رَسُوْلُ اللهِ وَ اَنَّ عَلِيًّا اَمِيْرُ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ وَ الْاَئِمَّةَ مِنْ وُلْدِهِ۔۔۔--This inscription may be written with water with which soil of Imam al-Husayn’s tomb or asba’ (apparently the soil of a certain mountain) is mixed. It must not be written with black color.", 
